dct_title_s: Caminos de Santiago en la Península Ibérica formado dibujado y publicado por el Instituto Geográfico Nacional ; con la colaboración de la Federación Española de Asociaciones de Amigos del Camino de Santiago.
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by gradient tints, shading, and spot heights. Depths shown by bathymetric tints and isolines. Map shows administrarive divisiion, roads and railroads. Caminos de Santiago was restored by iniciative of the Jacobian Associations. Shows 42 of the paths pilgrims take to the city of Santiago de Compostela, where many believe the remains of St. James were buried. Panel title. At head of title on map: Gobierno de España, Ministerio de Fomento, Instituto Geográfico Nacional. "Edita y comercializa: Centro Nacional de Información Geográfica." Includes index to 42 caminos de Santiago. Inset: Islas Canarias (España). Location map and map showing the regions of Spain on back panel. "Depósito legal: M-24835-2015." "NIPO 162-15-015-."
dct_publisher_sm: Madrid Centro Nacional de Información Geográfica 2015.
